An attacker came in and changed your data
You faced an MitM attack: An attacker positions themselves between
you and the server, intercepting, reading, and even modifying the
data without either side realizing it.
SOLVE THIS ISSUE
Client Server
By enabling TLS, you encrypt the communication between the client and
the server, which prevents attackers from intercepting or modifying the
data. So it effectively solves the Man-in-the-Middle attack issue.

✅A Certificate Authority (CA) is a trusted
company or organization that issues digital
certificates.
●A digital certificate proves who you are
(identity) on the internet.
● It’s used to secure websites (like HTTPS
🔒), emails, apps, etc.
●A CA basically says: "I guarantee this
website belongs to this company."

SSL-LAB
What is SSL Labs?
●SSL Labs is a free online tool created by Qualys.
●It helps you analyze and grade the SSL/TLS
security of a website.
Hands
On
SSL-LAB Hands
On
Grade Meaning:
A+ => Excellent. Very strong TLS setup + HSTS
configured.
A => Secure. Good modern TLS settings.
B => Some small weaknesses, but still okay.
C => Many problems. Unsafe for sensitive data.
F => Serious problems. Very insecure.
T (Test Failed) => The server didn’t pass basic
SSL/TLS checks (too bad to even grade).

OpenAI 4o
Comparing AI model results to Qualys SSL Labs, 70% of Gemini 2.0's
grades (203 out of 288) did not match, while 53% of OpenAI 4o's grades
(154 out of 288) did not align.
This indicates that the OpenAI 4o model is more aligned with SSL Labs than Gemini 2.0 —but neither model should be fully
trusted when it comes to security assessments (don’t use them for your cybersecurity homework — just kidding!).
This indicates that the OpenAI 4o model is more aligned with SSL Labs than Gemini 2.0 —but neither model should be fully
trusted when it comes to security assessments (don’t use them for your cybersecurity homework — just kidding!). This point
also extends to the broader AI vibe coders: while AI can be impressive at generating code, relying on it for security
configurations is not advisable. Improper configurations can easily occur. For security evaluations, it’s best to stick to
trusted tools like SSL Labs.
